@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{corfu-extras.el} extends @samp{corfu}, the lightweight completion-overlay package for Emacs. Corfu displays completion candidates in a popup at point, but two common workflow needs are not covered out of the box:

@itemize
@item
Enabling Corfu in the minibuffer without conflicting with @samp{vertico}, which also operates there (@ref{Minibuffer activation}).
@item
Transferring a Corfu completion session to the minibuffer for richer interaction via @samp{consult} (@ref{Transferring completion to the minibuffer}).
@end itemize

This package provides one function and one command addressing these needs. The transfer command requires the @samp{consult} package.

@node Functions
@chapter Functions

@menu
* Minibuffer activation::
@end menu

@node Minibuffer activation
@section Minibuffer activation

@findex corfu-extras-enable-always-in-minibuffer
When both Corfu and Vertico are installed, enabling Corfu unconditionally in the minibuffer would cause conflicts: both packages would attempt to display candidates simultaneously. The function @code{corfu-extras-enable-always-in-minibuffer} solves this by checking whether Vertico is active (via the internal variable @code{vertico--input}) before enabling @code{corfu-mode}.

This function is designed to be added to @code{minibuffer-setup-hook}. With it in place, Corfu provides completions in prompts like @samp{M-:} (@code{eval-expression}) and @samp{M-!} (@code{shell-command}), while Vertico remains in charge during @samp{M-x}, @code{find-file}, and other standard completing-read prompts.

This approach is adapted from Protesilaos Stavrou's configuration.

@node Commands
@chapter Commands

@menu
* Transferring completion to the minibuffer::
@end menu

@node Transferring completion to the minibuffer
@section Transferring completion to the minibuffer

@findex corfu-extras-move-to-minibuffer
Sometimes the Corfu popup is too constrained for the task at hand: you may want to filter candidates further, preview them, or use Consult's narrowing features. The command @code{corfu-extras-move-to-minibuffer} transfers the active Corfu completion session to the minibuffer by calling @code{consult-completion-in-region}. The completion boundaries, table, predicate, and extra properties are all preserved.

This command is automatically added to @code{corfu-continue-commands}, which means invoking it does not dismiss the Corfu popup prematurely. You can bind it to a key in @code{corfu-map} for convenient access while the popup is visible.

